77 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PURE GORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I suspected that Vidal, based on his behavior I've witnessed over the years via 
television, was a bit pompous. 
</P>
<P>
However, Harrison is the pretentious one, with her use of obscure words 
(jejune, probity, prescient). My favorite sentence: "Surely his woulds have had 
time to heal? They suppurate." I found Harrison's article revealing and 
entertaining, yet I got tired of having to stop so often to consult my 
dictionary. 
</P>
<P>
CAROL CHASTANG, Reseda 
</P>
</TEXT>
