<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: THE LAST WHALES BY LLOYD ABBEY (GROVE PRESS: $19.95; 352 PP.; 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Campbell Plowden 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Abbey's hypothesis -- that whales may survive only if the evolutionary meteor 
of the human species burns out sooner rather than later -- may not be so 
far-fetched." Campbell Plowden 
</P>
