<HEADLINE>
<P>
PANEL TO REVIEW SAN PEDRO BUSINESS DISTRICT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles City Councilwoman Joan Milke Flores has appointed a committee to 
review density, parking and planning design in the downtown San Pedro business 
district. The 23-member panel was appointed as part of an ongoing review of the 
San Pedro Community Plan. 
</P>
<P>
Insurance broker Curt Higgins will chair the new committee and attorney Bob 
Nizich was appointed vice chairman. The other members are Bess Akerson, 
community activist; Van Barbieri, real estate agent; Giuseppe Catalano, 
business owner; Ken Darling, architect; Dr. Robert Davies, physician; Fred 
DiBernardo, attorney; Al Galletti, hotel and business owner; Rick Gaydos, 
accountant; Janet Gunter, business owner; Ann Gushe, business owner; Ben 
Hudson, president of San Pedro Peninsula Chamber of Commerce; Gary Larson, 
developer; Roger Murry, businessman; Julie Nicosia, real estate agent; Nick 
Papadakis, business owner; Bill Pike, Realtor; Queenie Scheurwater, bank 
manager; Jim Trani, Sr., restaurateur; John Trutanich, developer and real 
estate agent; Mary Ann Walker, paralegal, and Thelma Zuanich, business owner. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Eidem, executive director of the San Pedro Revitalization Corp., and Len 
Betz, project manager for the local Community Redevelopment Agency, were named 
ex-officio members. 
</P>
<P>
The panel's first meeting, which will be open to the public, will be held at 
8:30 a.m. March 28 at Flores' San Pedro office, Room 200, 638 Beacon St. 
</P>
