<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN WORKING UNDER CAR INJURED IN HIT-AND-RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected drunk driver ended up doing the wrong thing at the wrong time 
Saturday morning when he slammed into a parked car, injuring a man working 
underneath it, then drove away as a Hawthorne police detective was driving 
past. 
</P>
<P>
The detective, who witnessed the incident at about 9:30 a.m., gave chase as the 
suspect drove away from the scene on Crenshaw Boulevard just south of Manhattan 
Beach Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Two Gardena police units helped stop the 1976 Pontiac Ventura several blocks 
away, Gardena Sgt. Tom Monson said. 
</P>
<P>
Gardena police arrested the driver, Christopher Russell, 24, of Redondo Beach, 
and booked him on suspicion of felony drunk driving and felony hit-and-run, 
Monson said. 
</P>
<P>
The injured man could not be identified, Monson said, because a police report 
that would provide that information had not yet been filed. Monson said the man 
was taken to Harbor General Hospital, where he was listed in satisfactory 
condition. 
</P>
