<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMENT ON PENSIONS HAS A FAMILIAR RING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the March 4 article "First Executive Casts a Shadow Over Pensions," an 
officer of First Executive states: "The company is in very robust financial 
health. Even suggesting we won't perform on (pension) obligations is 
far-fetched." This parallels the statements from their allies and 
partners-in-junk at Drexel Burnham Lambert who denied the filing-for-bankruptcy 
rumors the day before the actual occurrence. 
</P>
<P>
ALBERT C. FARRELL 
</P>
<P>
