<HEADLINE>
<P>
MODEL OF DISTRESS OVER DESIGNER'S STYLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re: "James Tarantino Makes Dressing Simply Elegant" (March 11). Elegant? 
"Clean, simple and pure?" Well, they are as simple as a flour sack with a hole 
slipped over the head. 
</P>
<P>
And people will pay hundreds of dollars for a back and front that I would whip 
together in an hour? Sack-cloth with buttons? 
</P>
<P>
I used to model, and I would not be caught dead in one of these. Methinks the 
Emperor had no clothes. I have been all over the world, and many countries have 
clothes that are more graceful, more colorful and (made of) more interesting 
material than we do. But few more expensive. 
</P>
<P>
CARYL C. BRADFORD, Arcadia 
