<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIMON IS TRAPPED, TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roger Simon assumes that because a court cannot prove child molestation that 
none existed. 
</P>
<P>
We all have heard of our imperfect court system. Known murderers are walking 
our streets due to plea-bargaining or suppression of sufficient evidence to win 
a prosecution. 
</P>
<P>
Child-molesters are released to continue to molest our children. 
</P>
<P>
It is the parent's moral duty to protect the child. That this could be at odds 
with a court decision is unfortunate and, yes, could cause illegal acts. 
</P>
<P>
Simon does not address the dilemma our courts and society are debating 
regarding the child-molestation problem. He chose to malign the tragic 
characters and thus does us all a disservice. 
</P>
<P>
PATRICIA BUCK, Whittier 
</P>
