<HEADLINE>
<P>
HELP STUDENTS PAY FOR TRIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Talolo and Joann Lepale, 16-year-old twins, students attending Bassett High 
School in La Puente, were selected as two of the 2,000 nationwide delegates to 
the Student Ambassador program (Times, March 4). 
</P>
<P>
Their 30-day tour of East Berlin, Poland, Holland, Russia, England is just 
another step towards peace and understanding in this ever shrinking world. 
</P>
<P>
These twins are fine examples of future potential community leaders. They are 
required to raise $8,000 between them, for air fare and housing, all within the 
next month or so! 
</P>
<P>
The citizens of our San Gabriel Valley are encouraged to support such positive 
and constructive youth programs. All financial contributions to the twins are 
an investment in the future of this nation. 
</P>
<P>
Please mail donations to: Robert F. Nero (principal), Bassett High School, 755 
N. Ardilla Ave., La Puente, Calif. 91746. 
</P>
<P>
The American Legion has long been a supporter of such worthwhile youth 
projects. The administrators at Bassett are to be commended for producing such 
fine representatives! 
</P>
<P>
TOM GOLDEN 
</P>
<P>
Assistant Adjutant 
</P>
<P>
American Legion Post 397 
</P>
<P>
Monterey Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
