<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKEWOOD TO AIR TAPE OF PIONEERS' GAME IN OAKLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Lakewood was so excited about its Artesia High School basketball 
team making it to the state championship game of the California Interscholastic 
Federation that the city sent a film crew to Oakland for the title game 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
A videotape of the game will be televised on Lakewood's cable Channel 31 today 
at 9 a.m. and 6 p.m. It will be shown again on Monday and Tuesday at 6 p.m. and 
on Wednesday and Thursday at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
The Pioneers earned the right to play for the state championship by first 
winning the Suburban League and 4-AA Southern Section Championships, as well as 
the Division 11 Southern California Championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
