<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENING; 
</P>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions on what to do in the garden this 
week from the California Assn. of Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Thin out the vegetable plants you may have started from seeds already to 
prevent overcrowding or stunted plants. 
</P>
<P>
Do this when they are 2 to 3 inches high. 
</P>
<P>
Give your lawn a boost this spring by starting a regular feeding program. 
</P>
<P>
"Pinch" annuals at planting time to produce bigger and better blooms later. 
</P>
<P>
Cut down on weeding time by applying mulch around plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
