<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNCIL HONORS HOME BUILDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ralph and Goldy Lewis, co-founders of Lewis Homes, Upland, have been named 1990 
Los Angeles Housing Persons of the Year by the National Housing Conference and 
will be honored at a June 27 dinner at the Century Plaza Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
The Washington, D.C.-based group, formed in 1931, is the oldest nonprofit 
bipartisan citizens' organization working for decent housing in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
The Lewises, who started their building firm in 1957, will be honored for their 
commitment, support and contributions to the housing industry. Eli Broad of 
Broad Inc./SunAmerica and John Lusk of the Lusk Co. are dinner co-chairman. 
Broad is a former Housing Person of the Year recipient. 
</P>
</TEXT>
