<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUBKA SETS INDOOR MARK AT 19-10 1/4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sergei Bubka of the Soviet Union broke his indoor world record in the pole 
vault Saturday, soaring 19 feet 10 1/4 inches during an international track and 
field meet in his Ukrainian hometown of Donetsk, Tass reported. 
</P>
<P>
Bubka, 26, improved his record by one inch. He set the previous mark of 19-9 
1/4 at Osaka, Japan, on Jan. 11, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Bubka, the Olympic and world outdoor champion, also owns the world outdoor 
record, 19-10 3/4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
