<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEASURING A GOOD SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Writers Guild of America appreciates good writing, whether or not it 
surfaces on a major network. Proof is the WGA nomination of "Measure of a Man," 
a beautiful script by Melinda M. Snodgrass for "Star Trek: The Next 
Generation." Now perhaps those behind the Emmy nominations will recognize the 
simply exquisite acting of Patrick Stewart, as well as the talents of the other 
people responsible for this fine series, one which consistently presents 
entertaining drama with comedic touches. 
</P>
<P>
Lynne Page, Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
