<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTORIST DODGES ERRANT DRIVER, RAMS CHP CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oceanside man swerving to miss a car that cut in front of him Saturday night 
rammed the back of a California Highway Patrol car parked on the side of 
Interstate 5 near the Camino de Estrella exit in San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
CHP Sgt. William Kelly said both the officer and the driver were taken to a 
local hospital, but neither was seriously injured and would probably be 
released. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly said the unidentified officer was stopped by the side of the road doing 
paper work when he was struck from behind. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, Ronald W. Radkovich, 45, said he was on his way home to Oceanside 
at 8:30 p.m. when he tried to evade a car that swerved into a lane in front of 
him. 
</P>
<P>
"I tried to get away from the other car. . . ," Radkovich said. "I hit my 
brakes, and I didn't see the (CHP car)." 
</P>
<P>
Radkovich's Cadillac was a total wreck and the rear of the CHP car was 
destroyed, Kelly said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
