<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI RALLIES TO BEAT SERVITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS KAISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mater Dei High School overcame an early deficit to defeat Servite, 7-4, in the 
Angelus League baseball opener for both teams Saturday at Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei (7-2 and the county's top-ranked team) took the lead for good in the 
fifth inning when Ryan Andersen singled with two outs and took second when the 
right fielder couldn't come up with the ball cleanly. 
</P>
<P>
Jim McCarthy drove in Andersen with a single. "We think we're a good team and 
they think they're a good team and this was the game to show it," Mater Dei 
Coach Bob Ickes said. "Both teams just came out tight and flat." 
</P>
<P>
Trailing 3-1, Mater Dei scored three runs in the third. 
</P>
<P>
In the fourth, Servite (5-3), the fourth-ranked team in the county, tried to 
start a rally, but Mater Dei got a double play after Steve Sandoval opened the 
inning with a single. The Friars only had three baserunners after that and none 
advanced past second base. 
</P>
<P>
Servite's Eddie Crippen hit a home run in the fifth to tie the score, 4-4. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei's Jason Dietrich gave up two runs in the first inning but settled 
down to get the victory. Dietrich (3-1) pitched five innings, giving up four 
runs, striking out five and walking one. Lionel Hastings struck out two in two 
shutout innings of relief. DENNIS KAISER 
</P>
</TEXT>
